{{infobox person |name=Helena Hamerow |birth_name=Helena Francisca Hamerow |birth_date={{birth date and age|1971|9|18}} |birth_place= |death_date= |death_place= |alma_mater=[[University of Oxford]] |occupation=[[Author]], [[professor]] }} '''Helena Francisca Hamerow''', [[Fellow of the Society of Antiquaries of London|FSA]] (born 18 September 1971)<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title = Birthdays | newspaper =[[The Guardian]] | location = | pages = 39 | language = | publisher = Guardian News & Media | date = 18 Sep 2014 }}</ref> is Professor of Early Medieval Archaeology and former Head of the [[School of Archaeology]] at [[Oxford University]]. She is the author of numerous books and academic articles on archaeology and early medieval history.
==Education and appointments== Hamerow obtained a BA from the [[University of Wisconsin-Madison]]<ref>[http://www.stx.ox.ac.uk/general/fellows/hamerow_helena_francisca St Cross College Fellows]</ref> and a DPhil from Oxford.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=TcuRJMDaZowC&pg=PR14 Book Biography]</ref> She was a research fellow at [[Somerville College, Oxford|Somerville College]] and a lecturer at [[Durham University]]. She is Professor of Early Medieval Archaeology and former Head of the School of Archaeology at Oxford University. She is a fellow of the [[Society of Antiquaries of London]].<ref>[http://www.sal.org.uk/history/listoffellows/?letter=H List of Fellows of the Society of Antiquaries, London] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101003032229/http://www.sal.org.uk/history/listoffellows/?letter=H |date=2010-10-03 }}</ref>
==Re-burial of excavated human remains== In 2011, Hamerow was one of forty leading archaeologists who wrote to the Justice Secretary, [[Kenneth Clarke]] asking for more time to study ancient human remains found in archaeological excavations.<ref>[http://uknewspapers.blogspot.com/2011/02/guardian-news_04.html Letter to the Guardian newspaper]</ref>
==Media== Hamerow has appeared on ''[[Digging for Britain]]'', ''[[King Alfred and the Anglo Saxons]]'' and 2 episodes of ''[[Time Team]].{{citation needed|date=October 2017}}
