{{Infobox artwork | title = Hercules and Antaeus | image_file = BLW Hercules and Antaeus.jpg | painting_alignment = | image_size = | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | type = [[bronze sculpture]] with [[silver]] [[gilding]] | artist = [[Pier Jacopo Alari Bonacolsi]] (El Antico) | year = {{circa}} 1500–1510 | catalogue = A.37–1956 | height_metric = 40.8 | width_metric = 22 | height_imperial = | width_imperial = | condition = | city = [[London]] | museum = [[Victoria and Albert Museum]] | coordinates = | owner = | accession = | url = {{URL|https://collections.vam.ac.uk/item/O94280/hercules-and-antaeus-figure-group-antico/}} }}
'''Hercules and Antaeus''' is an early 16th-century bronze sculpture by [[Pier Jacopo Alari Bonacolsi|Pier Jacopo di Antonio Alari-Bonacolsi]]. The [[House of Gonzaga|Gonzaga family]] court sculptor based this group on a classical marble of Hercules and Antaeus which is now in the [[Palazzo Pitti|Pitti Palace]] in [[Florence]]. The statue was given to the Victoria and Albert Museum by Dr. W. L. Hildburgh, F. S. A., in 1956.<ref>{{cite web| publisher=Victoria and Albert Museum| accessdate=2014-07-11| title=Herculas and Antaeus| url=https://collections.vam.ac.uk/item/O94280/hercules-and-antaeus-figure-group-antico/}}</ref>
