{{refimprove|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox artwork | title = Mrs. Schuyler Van Rensselaer (Mariana Griswold) | painting_alignment = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | wikidata =Q28229021 | image = Mrs. Schuyler Van Rensselaer (Mariana Griswold) MET DT94.jpg | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | artist = [[Augustus Saint-Gaudens]] | year = 1888, cast 1890 | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | catalogue = | medium = [[Bronze sculpture]] | movement = | subject = [[Mariana Griswold Van Rensselaer]] | height_metric = 51.8 | width_metric = 19.7 | length_metric = | diameter_metric = | height_imperial = 20 3/8 | width_imperial = 7 3/4 | length_imperial = | diameter_imperial = | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | metric_unit = cm <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = in <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | weight = | designation = | condition = | museum = [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] | city = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S. | coordinates = <!-- Only use for the coordinates (when known) of the artwork itself, i.e. not for the site, building, structure, etc where it is kept, otherwise leave blank (or omit): {{coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | owner = | accession = 17.104 | preceded_by = <!-- preceding work by the same artist --> | followed_by = <!-- next work by the same artist --> | module = | website = <!-- Official webpage/site only: {{URL|example.com}} --> }} {{italic title|noerror|all=yes}} <!-- template after the infobox to prevent the display of error message --> '''''Mrs. Schuyler Van Rensselaer (Mariana Griswold)''''' is a [[bronze sculpture]] by American artist [[Augustus Saint-Gaudens]]. It was designed in 1888 and cast in 1890. This artwork portrays the American author, art critic, and reformer [[Mariana Griswold Van Rensselaer]] (1851–1934), who "championed Saint-Gaudens in articles on his public monuments and relief sculptures".<ref name="MET">{{cite web|url=http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/works-of-art/17.104/|title=Mrs. Schuyler Van Rensselaer (Mariana Griswold) - Augustus Saint-Gaudens - 17.104 - Work of Art - Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History - The Metropolitan Museum of Art|publisher=}}</ref>
The inscription on the upper center of the sculpture, ''animvs non opvs'' ("the spirit, not the work") is a reference to Mrs. Van Rensselaer’s "high-minded aesthetic ideals".<ref name="MET"/>
The work was given in 1917 by the sitter to the [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]].<ref name="MET"/>
